blog.name: angelofberlin2000
blog.title: Like a Rose trampled on the ground
blog.description:
In addition to the pain and the exhaustion, he recalled how waiting on the cross between takes became tedious. To fight the boredom, he listened to music on headphones. One particular song called "Above All" (Like a Rose ...) by Michael W. Smith helped him through his most difficult moments.

"It arrived when I was confused and angry. I didn't think I could go on. The song described how Jesus was rejected and alone. That thought took me to a place — it opened an interior door that held me while on the cross," an emotional Caviezel explained. "The experience of feeling rejected and alone as all those around me laughed while drinking their hot coffees, oblivious to what was occurring. Jesus must have felt like this — forsaken, rejected, alone, and despised. It helped me pray in a very deep way — to pray without words, to pray from the heart. The discomfort, the loneliness, the split shoulder, the raw flesh all forced me into the arms of God because I had nowhere else to go for a performance I knew I was unable to create."
Jim Caviezel, Shamelessly Catholic

body:
Unwanted movie review time!

I think I'mma continue doing these. I quite enjoy writing my opinions :P

So, The Matrix. The movie is 2 years younger than me. I’ve known about it’s existence forever but I never watched it. Until now. What inspired me? The precious boy himself. I’ve seen Matrix memes and all, I knew the music, bullet dodging. All that jazz. Never actually watched. @natashayess got live commentary as per her request. I hope she wasn’t disappointed. I liked the movie quite a bit. Not sure if I’ll rewatch any time soon, plus I have the sequels to watch. Whatever I may have thought that the movie would be about through the years… this wasn’t it xD To be honest with the way we’re going now the movie’s plotline isn’t that far off from a possible future. Creepy robot squids and the teacer bug gave ne the heebie jeebies. Too many eyes and tentacles. Not bad fighting scenes. My favourite has to be when Neo and Trinity have an all out shoot out with the soldiers in the lobby. Were you really fighting if you didn’t wreck the whole place? Neo’s all black outfits were on point. When I saw him in the black suit my mind went ‘Baby Wick’ instinctively. I’m excuted to watch the sequel. I hope I’m not disappointed.
